==English==

===Etymology===
From {{ME.}} ''[[declenson]]'', from {{MF.}} ''[[declinaison]]'' (French: ''[[déclinaison]]''), from {{L.}} ''[[declination]]''.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# {{grammar}}: A way of categorizing [[noun]]s, [[pronoun]]s, or [[adjective]]s according to the inflections they receive.
#: ''In Latin, 'amicus' belongs to the second declension. Most second-declension nouns end in 'i' in the genitive singular and 'um' in the accusative singular.''
# {{grammar}}: The act of [[declining]] a word; the act of listing the [[inflection]]s of a noun, pronoun or adjective in order.

